23/05/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski and his Croatian counterpart, Ivo Sanader, announced on Monday (22 May) that they are boosting the level of bilateral co-operation in efforts to join Euro-Atlantic structures. 
The two met during Sanader's official visit to Skopje. 
They agreed that the EU enlargement process must not stop with the accession of Bulgaria and Romania but must proceed with the rest of Southeast Europe, to ensure stability and prosperity in the region. 
Sanader and Buckovski reiterated that their governments expect a clear sign about membership prospects during NATO's November summit in Riga. 
(HINA, HRT, Telma TV, Makfax - 22/05/06)
